  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study in patients suffering from acute lung injury is to determine
      whether positive end-expiratory pressure (PEEP) setting guided by electrical impedance
      tomography (EIT) influences pulmonary gas exchange, lung mechanics, ventilation/perfusion
      matching and homogeneity of regional ventilation when compared to other PEEP setting
      strategies such as the open lung concept or the ARDSnet protocol.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
